  "uuid": "6b1d8e4d2c063806c46657e227e7a5a4",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Customer Service Executive",
  "description": "<p>At Silver Bullion, we pride ourselves on helping our clients Truly Protect Their Wealth across the globe by minimizing their exposure to systemic risks via precious metals. As we expand our reach, we’re seeking dedicated and enthusiastic individuals to join our team as Customer Service Executives. If you're passionate about wealth protection and thrive in a fast-paced environment, we'd love to hear from you!</p><p><br />Responsibilities</p><p><ul><li>Provide outstanding customer support via phone, email, and chat in English, helping clients make their precious metal transactions.</li><li>Assist customers with inquiries, complaints, product information, and general issues in a professional manner.</li><li>Resolve customer issues efficiently, ensuring a positive customer experience.</li><li>Collaborate with internal teams to escalate and solve complex problems.</li><li>Accurately document customer interactions and maintain detailed records of customer inquiries.</li><li>Potentially working in the early mornings as you will be serving mostly customers from North America, Canada and Australia.</li><li>Stay updated on product offerings and company policies to provide accurate and timely information to customers.</li></ul></p><p><br />Qualifications</p><ul><li><p>Strong proficiency in English for speaking and writing required. Other languages is a plus. </p></li><li><p>Previous experience in customer service, call center, or a similar role is a plus</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal.</p></li><li><p>Strong problem-solving abilities and a proactive approach to customer issues.</p></li><li><p>Ability to multitask and manage time effectively in a high-pressure environment.</p></li><li><p>Tech-savvy with knowledge of CRM systems and basic computer skills.</p></li></ul>",
